The paper discusses unsupervised representation learning, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on learning feature representations that are useful in downstream classification tasks. The paper also discusses text and image domains, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper introduces a theoretical framework for analyzing the algorithms, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories.
